    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">How much do solar panels cost in Iowa?</h3>
    <p>Solar panel costs in Iowa typically range from \$2.20 to \$2.65 per watt before incentives. For a typical residential system, homeowners can expect to pay \$11,500-14,000 for a 5kW system or \$22,000-26,500 for a 10kW system before applying the federal tax credit. After the 30% federal tax credit, these costs drop to \$8,050-9,800 and \$15,400-18,550 respectively. Installation costs vary based on roof complexity, system size, and local permitting requirements, but Iowa's streamlined solar permitting processes help keep costs competitive with national averages.</p>
  </div>
  
