    <p>For Iowa's climate, HVAC systems with SEER ratings of 16 or higher are recommended for optimal efficiency and comfort. While the minimum federal standard is 14 SEER, Iowa's hot, humid summers and substantial cooling loads make higher-efficiency systems worthwhile investments. Systems with 16-18 SEER ratings provide excellent performance for most Iowa homes, while 20+ SEER systems offer maximum efficiency for homeowners prioritizing energy savings. The higher upfront cost of high-SEER systems is typically recovered through lower electricity bills over the system's 15-20 year lifespan.</p>
  </div>
  
